== Farebae ==
Wɔ Hella Kyerɛwnsɛm a ɛwɔ kane Greek kasa mu no, asɛmfua a ɛne porneia (πορνεία - <nowiki>''</nowiki>Adwamanbo) no puei mpen 25 (a wɔde asɛmfua πορνεία no gyina ho ma Adwmammɔ no<ref>Strong's Greek: 4202. πορνεία (porneia) -- 25 Occurrences (biblehub.com)</ref>.


Wɔ afeha a ɛtɔ so nnan no mu no, Latin Vulgate a ɛyɛ Latin nkyerɛase nhoma a ɛkyerɛ Greek nsɛmfua ase no kyerɛ asɛmfua no ase sɛ ''fornicati'', ''fornicatus'', ''fornicata'', ne ''fornicatae''. Asemfua Adwammo ne adwamanbofo ye nea epuei wɔ afe 1599 Geneva Kyerewnsem mu, afe 1611 kyrewnsem a ɛne King James no mu, Catholic Rheims Kyerɛwnsɛm ne 1901 kyerɛwnsɛm a ɛde American Standard Version no mu<ref>Matthew 5:32 - Wikipedia</ref><ref>1 Corinthians 6.9 ''fornicators'' in GNV, KJV, DRA</ref>. Kyerɛwnsɛm ahorɔw a ɛbaa wɔ wiase ko a ɛtɔ so mienu no akyi no yɛ nea w'akati asɛmfua a ɛne Adwamammo ne adwamammɔfo. Kyerɛwnsɛm a ɛne [[:en:English_Standard_Version|English Standard Version]], [[:en:New_Living_Translation|New Living Translation]], [[:en:New_International_Version|New International Version]], [[:en:Christian_Standard_Bible|Christian Standard Bible]], [[:en:Good_News_Bible|Good News Bible]] and [[:en:Contemporary_English_Version|Contemporary English Version]] yɛ nea wɔnfa asɛmfua adwamammɔ anaa adwmammɔfo nni dwuma<ref>SQL database search for terms ''fornication'' or ''fornicators'' in respective Bible Translations.</ref>. Sɛ nkyerɛase baako de asɛmfua Adwammɔ di dwuma no, nkyerɛase foforo de asɛmfua a te sɛ nna mu ɔbrasei (Nhwɛso wɔ Mateo 19;9), anaa tiawa no, wɔ ɔbrasei di dwuma<ref>The English Standard Version : Christian Courier</ref><ref>Porneia Meaning in Bible - New Testament Greek Lexicon - King James Version (biblestudytools.com)</ref><ref>1 Corinthians 6.9 RSV (immoral) vs KJV (fornicators)</ref>.

Wɔ Latin kasa mu no, asɛmfua a ɛne Fornix no kyerɛ kankofa<ref>Internet Archive: Error</ref>. Wɔ tete Rome no, adwamanfoɔ yɛ nea wɔtwɛn adwadifoɔ no wɔ kankofa no ase senea nsuo nhwe wɔn, na ɛno na ɛmaa asɛmfua kankofa no begyinaa hɔ maa tuutuudan anaa agyantrafoɔfie<ref>Ancient Rome in So Many Words - Christopher Francese - Google Books</ref><ref>The Merriam-Webster new book of word histories : Merriam-Webster, Inc : Free Download, Borrow, and Streaming : Internet Archive</ref><ref>Oxford English Dictionary - Wikipedia</ref>, na Latin asɛmfua a ɛne fonicare no gyina hɔ ma ɔbirima a ɔkɔ agyantrafoɔfie. Kyerɛwtohɔ a edikan wɔ Brɔfo kasa no mu yɛ nea ɛwɔ Cursor Mundi, c. 1300; Nnwoma a ɛde Oxford Dictionary no nso de sɛnea wɔde ne kasakoa di dwuma;<ref>Oxford English Dictionary - Wikipedia</ref><ref>Oxford English Dictionary - Wikipedia</ref>  

